
1. List all services.
kubectl get svc

2. Describe a specific service.
kubectl describe svc

3. Fetches and displays a list of Kubernetes services (abbreviated as svc), -o wide adds extra information to the output.
   Like information related to ClusterIP, ExternalP, Ports and other.
kubectl get svc -o wide

4. Outputs the service details in YAML format.
kubectl get svc -o yaml

5. Adds a column to the output that displays the labels assigned to each service.
kubectl get svc --show-labels